                <p>[<hi rend="italic">N. B.—The summary of this correspondence is omitted. It mainly
                        relates to the doctrine of perpetual allegiance, which was abandoned by
                        Congress in the act of</hi> 1868, (15 <hi rend="italic">Statutes at
                        Large</hi>, 223,) <hi rend="italic">and which has also been abandoned by
                        Great Britain and other powers with whom we have treaties of
                        naturalization</hi>.]</p>
